ikmatyar offered to shelter [[Usama bin Laden]] after he later fled Sudan in 1996.<ref name=ArbNasratKhan>[{{DoD detainees ARB|ARB_Transcript_Set_10_21352-21661.pdf#257}} Summarized transcript (.pdf)], from [[Hajji|Haji]] [[Nasrat Khan]]'s ''[[Administrative Review Board]] hearing'' \u2013 pages 257-265</ref>\n|-\n|\n* [[Mohamed Jawad]]\n||\n* ''The Hezb-E-Islami ''{{Sic}}'' organization is a terrorist organization with long-established ties to [[Osama bin Laden|Bin Laden]].<ref name=FoiEvidenceMemoMohamedJawad>\n[http://www.defenselink.mil/pubs/foi/detainees/csrt_mar05.pdf#149 Summary of Evidence (.pdf)], from [[Mohamed Jawad]]'s ''[[Combatant Status Review Tribunal]]''\nOctober 19, 2004 \u2013 page 149</ref>\n|-\n|\n* [[Juma Din]]\n||\n* ''HIG is a designated terrorist group with long-established links to [[Usama Bin Laden]].<ref name=CsrtJumaDin>[{{DoD detainees ARB|Set_21_1645-1688_Revised.pdf#38}} Summarized transcripts (.pdf)], from [[Juma Din]]'s ''[[Combatant Status Review Tribunal]]'' \u2013 pages 38-44</ref>\n|-\n|\n* [[Akhtiar Mohammad (Guantanamo detainee 1036)|Akhtiar Mohammad]]\n||\n* ''The HiG is listed in the [[Terrorist Organization Reference Guide]] as having long-established ties with [[Usama Bin Laden]].<ref name=CsrtAkhtiarMohammad1036>\n[{{DoD detainees ARB|Set_13_1240-1291.pdf#43}} Summarized transcripts (.pdf)], from [[Akhtiar Mohammad (Guantanamo detainee 1036)|Akhtiar Mohammad]]'s''[[Combatant Status Review Tribunal]]'' \u2013 pages 43-52</ref>\n|-\n|\n* [[Faizullah (Guantanamo captive 919)|Faiz Ullah]]\n||\n* ''The '''Hizb-I Islami Gulbuddin''' ''{{Sic}}'' (HIG) has been identified as an organization which sponsor terrorism.<ref name=CsrtSummaryOfEvidence287>[http://www.dod.mil/pub/foi/detainees/csrt_Mar05.pdf#89 Summary of Evidence memo (.pdf)] prepared for [[Faizullah (Guantanamo captive 919)|Faiz Ullah]]'s ''[[Combatant Status Review Tribunal]]'' \u2013 October 15, 2004 \u2013 page 89</ref>\n|-\n|\n* [[Jumma Jan]]\n||\n* ''HIG has been 